column1: COVID robbed us of a normal Thanksgiving but it cannot stop us from giving thanks this year.   Let’s give thanks to the doctors & nurses who fought this virus on the front lines the essential workers who risked their safety to provide Americans with vital services...

As COVID cases rise and Thanksgiving gets closer many food pantries are struggling to meet unprecedented demand. When you buy groceries this week consider donating some non-perishable foods to your local pantry.
This is not a normal holiday season and we still need to take appropriate precautions to protect ourselves and our loved ones from COVID. It is not easy but it is necessary. https://t.co/FtHlNvfDkX

The second wave of COVID is here and it could not come at a worse time. This is not going to be a normal holiday season. We need to remember that this pandemic will not take time off on Thanksgiving. We still need to socially distance limit gatherings and use common sense. https://t.co/yKgWLQ8oIF
As cases rise again in New Jersey we need to get back into the fight against COVID by wearing masks and practicing social distancing. We can do this. https://t.co/qax41gLWq5

Republicans are spending more time soothing Donald Trump’s ego than at passing a COVID recovery package. The election is over and it is time to come together and beat this pandemic.   https://t.co/XvdfdOMqXs

“It’s just a failure to do their job and to govern because they’re so focused on trying to undermine the election” said Pallone “I do believe it hinders efforts to pass the bill...they’re not focusing on legislation to deal with the COVID crisis.”  https://t.co/iYcdrnfQOw
@MikieSherrill is an outstanding Congresswoman and has been indispensable in protecting our healthcare and fighting for more COVID relief. We need her in Congress. https://t.co/YjadaYTkPH

While Senate Republicans pat themselves on the back for confirming a new Supreme Court justice millions of people are struggling to feed their families and pay rent because the GOP refuses to take up the House's COVID relief bill.
Honored to have the endorsement of @JNESODC1’s 5000 professional healthcare workers who are on the frontlines of fighting COVID. https://t.co/EDRwCgNWTd

If we had a national testing plan and a President who took this virus seriously we would be prepared for another wave of COVID. Instead Donald Trump left us exposed and vulnerable. Vote him out.   https://t.co/iS2oWX6HJn

This is profoundly irresponsible. The President was just hospitalized for COVID-19. We don’t know when he got his last negative test. He should not be going out in front of people in public without a mask. He just does not take this virus seriously.  https://t.co/noA8bqaHLM
Donald Trump and the Senate Republicans have been sitting on COVID-19 relief bills for months. People are going hungry. Their cruelty must be rebuked on November 3rd.  https://t.co/7rnSBm0uNa

New Jersey is leading the way on COVID testing and tracing. Download the state’s #COVIDAlertNJ app to know if you’ve potentially been exposed to coronavirus and join the fight against this pandemic. https://t.co/lSG90Lip5F
